MyBroadband has revealed its Mobile Network Quality Report looking at the Q1 2018 performance of South Africa’s four major mobile networks. Based on 142,537 mobile network speed tests, the results show that MTN is currently South Africa’s fastest network, with an average download speed of 24.12Mbps. MTN also claimed top spot in MyBroadband’s Network Quality Score rankings, meaning it has the best mobile network in South Africa – based on a range of performance measurements. For MTN users, this means reaping the benefits of incredible streaming and great download and upload speeds. Download the latest music from MTN MusicPlus on your mobile or desktop. <span data-mce-type="bookmark" style="display: inline-block; width: 0px; overflow: hidden; line-height: 0;" class="mce_SELRES_start">﻿</span> Load, connect, and stream the latest games using MTNGamer+. <span data-mce-type="bookmark" style="display: inline-block; width: 0px; overflow: hidden; line-height: 0;" class="mce_SELRES_start">﻿</span> This article was published in partnership with MTN.